messages.messageBody:
-=-Argh! I'm hooked-=-

I was working on a blog post about it here (Joyce, that was a great
find. Thank you)
http://thinkingsticks.blogspot.com

And my browser froze up. Sheeesh. Just because I had about 25
windows open, some trying to load things...

I do remember when browsers could have ONE window open. And I
remember when computers weren't hooked to anything but electricity
and maybe a daisy-wheel printer. So I take a deep breath and
relaunch. <g>

I'm going back there now.

Sandra

Oh, great! Thanks. Now nobody will post to this list or read on my
website all weekend because that blog is way too awesome! (I don't
mind a bit; it's very cool and I subscribed.)

I thought you were going to post something about the book Kluge,
which I started reading and then left lying somewhere where a
paperdrift covered it and I might not find it until next Spring.
(Yeah, I better not be on Wife Swap because my paper-and-book
geological formations are fun for dating how long they've been there
by the dates on the receipts or movie tickets at the bottom, but
they're not very photogenic.





Sandra

messages.subject: Crooked Brains
messages.msgSnippet: I stumbled across a site chock full of fascinating pictures. She posts a half dozen to a dozen photos in various categories: Colorful Dogs, Interesting Hair
messages.messageBody:
I stumbled across a site chock full of fascinating pictures. She
posts a half dozen to a dozen photos in various categories: Colorful
Dogs, Interesting Hair Designs, Ads Using Pillows. There are links
for further browsing and links to related posts.

It could easily suck up hours :-)

http://www.crookedbrains.net/

If you enter your email into "Get updates by email" you'll get each
new full blog post with pictures and links.

Joyce
